<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1879] ReadOnly transactions generate WAL activity.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1879</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently we write a start entry in the WAL each time a transaction starts, and a commit/abort at the end of the transaction. This means read-only transactions unnecessarily generate two WAL entries per region.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can avoid this by removing the start entry from the WAL (this is implicit in the first trx OP entry we see), and only writing commit/abort when the transaction has a write.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
